- The document provides details about the eligibility criteria for receiving Sumbangan Asas Rahmah (SARA) assistance. It is available to Warga Malaysia, Lulus Sembilan Rumah Tetap (STR), and individuals without a spouse in Sabah or Sarawak who have been granted Mendapatkan Tunai Rahmah 2026 but are not married yet;
- The eligibility criteria include being born as Warga Malaysia, having received the Sumbangan Asas Rahmah (SARA) assistance before and after marriage for a continuous period of at least six months within two years prior to application submission or during pregnancy/childbirth. However, it does not apply if you are married;
- The document also mentions that eligibility is extended to those who have been granted Mendapatkan Tunai Rahmah 2026 but did not receive the full amount due to insufficient funds or other reasons and were unable to complete their studies, with a specific mention of an additional RM150 for each child born after January 1st, 2023.
- The document also outlines that eligibility is limited based on age (below the age of 64) and marital status; single individuals are prioritized over married ones or those with a spouse in Sabah/Sarawak for this program. It further specifies an income ceiling, where applicants must earn less than RM250 per month to qualify.
- Lastly, the document states that eligibility is also based on whether one has been granted Mendapatkan Tunai Rahmah 2026 before or during pregnancy/childbirth and if they have not received any other form of assistance for at least six months prior to application.
- The Sumbangan Asas Rahmah (SARA) program is a conditional cash transfer scheme aimed at assisting the poorest households in Malaysia, with priority given based on age, marital status and income level among other factors as per JPM's regulations.
